{"tid":2380262,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"<Made in China> 美國新政府 阻止香港升級WTO貿易爭端","createTime":"2021-01-25T17:54:40.000Z","updateTime":"2021-01-26T01:01:12.000Z","uid":227801,"like":13,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"8c3dda432dd9578384a7bf74a628e296e335acb1","tid":2380262,"uid":227801,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-25T17:54:40.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-trade-wto-hongkong/u-s-blocks-hong-kongs-escalation-of-wto-trade-dispute-idUSKBN29U1NA\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-trade-wto-hongkong%2Fu-s-blocks-hong-kongs-escalation-of-wto-trade-dispute-idUSKBN29U1NA&d=KsvwSKeUMZz4C4B35sIM%2BA5Iyec62GFiithg4eFnous%3D&h=fd5f5a5b\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-trade-wto-hongkong%2Fu-s-blocks-hong-kongs-escalation-of-wto-trade-dispute-idUSKBN29U1NA&h=0d846174\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/us-trade-wto-hongkong/u-s-blocks-hong-kongs-escalation-of-wto-trade-dispute-idUSKBN29U1NA</a><br />\n(Reuters) - The United States on Monday blocked a decision by Hong Kong to escalate a Trump-era trade disagreement at the World Trade Organization, in its first meeting on disputes at the Geneva-based body since U.S. President Joe Biden's inauguration.<br />\nSpeaking at the WTO's closed-door dispute settlement body, the U.S. delegate opposed Hong Kong's decision to escalate the dispute by creating a WTO panel to rule on it, according to a copy of the speech.<br />\nHowever, Washington can only block it once and Hong Kong, a member in its own right at the 164-member body, can raise it again at the WTO next month.<br />\n<br />\nThe so-called &quot;Made in China&quot; dispute, opened by Hong Kong on Nov. 3, is over a U.S. rule stipulating that goods from the special administrative region of China now be marked as coming from China.<br />\nThis requirement was announced by U.S. Customs and Border Protection in August, breaking with a former policy that allowed Hong Kong to be named as a place of origin.<br />\nThe closed-door meeting of the WTO's dispute settlement body on Monday was Washington's first chance to weigh in on long-standing active trade disputes as well as deadlocked talks over revamping the WTO's top appeals bench.<br />\nUnder former President Donald Trump, Washington blocked new judge appointments to the Appellate Body in a bid to force through reforms. However, it signalled no change in its position on the body at the Monday meeting and declined to support a proposal to appoint new judges.<br />\nWhile Biden's administration has officially taken over trade policy, observers say they do not expect any big changes until after Biden's trade nominee, Katherine Tai, is confirmed."},{"pid":"86fc3e90d084708b073f09b227b633af0b7cbb52","tid":2380262,"uid":227801,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-25T17:59:50.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/mouse/tea.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2efc908ea49953fdd92e81cebb59a474ca760e99","tid":2380262,"uid":2300,"like":16,"dislike":1,"score":15,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-25T18:01:02.000Z","msg":"fake news 無可能的<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/KtM8UWD.gif\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FKtM8UWD.gif&h=901c5e7d&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"ca51fe9975d55fb82027618645adcae577f0798e","tid":2380262,"uid":225931,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-25T18:07:30.000Z","msg":"Made in china 好失禮咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/aura.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2412a4a67da5dcdab3a407a79c94b48fff42d36d","tid":2380262,"uid":8014,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"2efc908ea49953fdd92e81cebb59a474ca760e99","tid":2380262,"uid":2300,"like":16,"dislike":1,"score":15,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-25T18:01:02.000Z","msg":"fake news 無可能的<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/KtM8UWD.